title: UARX Partners with Sener to Continue Development of OSSIE OTV
summary:
Spanish space transportation startup UARX Space has partnered with the multinational engineering and technology group Sener to assist with the development of the company’s OSSIE orbital transfer vehicle (OTV). OSSIE (Orbit Solutions to Simplify Injection and Exploration) is designed to be capable of performing a number of missions, including satellite delivery, debris removal, and in-orbit […]

title: Kayhan raises $7 million and offers autonomous traffic-coordination service
summary: Kayhan Space raised $7 million in an extension to the spaceflight safety startup’s seed round and unveiled an autonomous space-traffic coordination framework.

title: Rocket Lab stock drops after first satellite launch failure in over two years
summary: Rocket Lab stock fell after the company suffered its first launch failure in over two years early Tuesday morning.

title: Electron fails during Capella Space launch
summary: A Rocket Lab Electron failed during a launch of Capella Space radar imaging satellite Sept. 19.

title: DEVELOPING STORY: RocketLab Electron Launch Failure
summary: RocketLab's 41st Electron mission "We Will Never Desert You" has ended in a launch failure due the failure of the 2nd stage.
